description: Nagpur Municipal Corporation (NMC) has temporarily paused demolitions linked to riot accused following a Bombay High Court stay, continuing investigations into property irregularities. Authorities focus on verifying legal ownership and unauthorized constructions. Despite the stay, NMC continues cross-checking records to avoid legal missteps, with future actions pending the court's final verdict.

description: The law ministry revealed that around 78% of judges appointed to high courts since 2018 were from upper castes, with 5% each from minorities and SC/ST, and 12% from OBC. The government emphasizes the need for social diversity and has requested the judiciary to consider this in judicial appointments.
title: Govt: 78% judges appointed to HCs from upper castes

description: Russia and Ukraine have agreed to halt military actions in the Black Sea and on energy infrastructure after US-mediated talks in Riyadh. The agreement includes safe navigation and a ban on using commercial vessels for military purposes. However, Russia stipulates that the deal will be effective only if Western restrictions on its agricultural sector are lifted, with the US offering concessions on Russian agriculture trade.

SC orders scrutiny of Apollo over EWS intake
Uttarakhand government schoolkids say 'ni hao' to Mandarin

description: The BJP government in Delhi has presented a Rs 1 lakh crore budget for 2025-26, significantly increasing the allocation for education, transport, and health. Chief Minister Rekha Gupta outlined financial support for women's grants, Ayushman Bharat, and water and sanitation projects, highlighting a focused drive towards infrastructure and social welfare enhancements.
title: With a record 32% hike, Rekha Gupta presents Rs 1L crore budget for Delhi

description: The Supreme Court has ruled that cutting a large number of trees is worse than killing a human being, imposing a fine of Rs 1 lakh per tree for illegal felling. The court set a benchmark for penalties in such cases, refusing to reduce the fine for a man who illegally cut down 454 protected trees.
title: Cutting large number of trees worse than killing a human being, says Supreme Court
India, China hold ‘positive’ round of border talks

description: S Jaishankar, India's External Affairs Minister, met with UN Special Envoy Julie Bishop in Delhi to discuss border stability, the refugee situation, transnational crime, and economic support for Myanmar. Their discussions also covered the political situation in Myanmar, underscoring the importance of cooperation in various sectors to enhance bilateral trade and stability in the region.
title: Jaishankar discusses border security with UN secretary general's special envoy on Myanmar

description: The Odisha assembly witnessed high drama as 12 suspended Congress MLAs refused to vacate the Well of the House, demanding an inquiry into crimes against women during BJP's rule. Speaker Surama Padhy suspended them for indiscipline. Despite their protests, including playing gongs and chanting, attempts to resolve the issue through an all-party meeting failed.

description: The latest episode of Celebrity MasterChef saw an emotional eviction as Usha Nadkarni, known as the Maa of MasterChef, was eliminated. Despite her efforts in cooking a fish dish, the judges found it overcooked. Both Usha and her fellow contestant Faisu, who suggested the mystery box, were deeply emotional. The judges and crew gave her a heartfelt farewell.

description: Shreyas Iyer led Punjab Kings to a thrilling 11-run victory over Gujarat Titans in their IPL 2025 opener. Iyer's unbeaten 97 and tactical leadership helped Punjab set a massive 243/5. Gujarat's chase fell short despite strong efforts from their batsmen. Iyer’s selfless gameplay and strategic thinking earned him the Player of the Match title. Punjab Kings will next face Lucknow Super Giants on April 1 at the Ekana Cricket Stadium in Lucknow.

description: A recent notice by Secretary of State Marco Rubio reclassifies immigration policies as 'foreign-affairs functions,' allowing them to bypass public notice and comment requirements. This move could enable rapid regulatory changes with minimal oversight, impacting high-skilled immigrants, particularly Indian nationals, amidst expected legal challenges.

description: Canada’s Express Entry system will no longer grant additional points for job offers starting March 25. This change aims to reduce fraud and impacts CRS scores for all candidates, including those currently in the pool. The decision encourages genuine applications and aligns with Canada's 2025-2027 levels plan.

description: On the eve of Rajasthan Royals' IPL 2025 match against Kolkata Knight Riders, RR head coach Rahul Dravid, currently in a wheelchair due to injury, had a heartwarming interaction with KKR players. Both teams aim for a turnaround after recent losses. Dravid, despite his injury, remains dedicated to RR’s campaign, reflecting his enduring resilience.

description: Three individuals were injured following a mid-air collision of two French Air Force jets near Saint-Dizier, northeastern France. Both pilots and a passenger ejected and were found conscious. Emergency services responded immediately to the scene, and no civilian casualties were reported despite one jet crashing into a silo and sparking a fire.

description: Atishi, opposition leader in Delhi assembly, criticized the BJP government for slashing funds in key sectors like education and health in its budget. She claimed the move aimed to weaken public services and accused the government of hiding the Economic Survey to avoid revealing the 'hollow budget.' Atishi called the budget a 'jumla' and demanded the real figures be presented.

description: AIADMK general secretary Edappadi K Palaniswami visited Union home minister Amit Shah amidst speculation of renewing alliances for the upcoming assembly polls. AIADMK had previously severed ties with BJP due to growing ambitions and controversial remarks. Their tumultuous partnership history includes alliances and significant electoral losses, yet they intermittently collaborated since 1998.

description: Punjab Kings set a new T20 record at Narendra Modi Stadium with a massive total of 243/5 against Gujarat Titans in IPL 2025. Skipper Shreyas Iyer led with an unbeaten 97 off 42 balls, while Shashank Singh's 44 off 16 balls added a late flourish. Priyansh Arya's explosive start and aggressive middle-overs batting powered PBKS to a formidable score.

description: US President Donald Trump rejected calls to fire National Security Advisor Michael Waltz after a security lapse involving an unsecured app to coordinate military strikes in Yemen. description: Prashant Kishor, leader of Jan Suraaj Party, has demanded a medical bulletin for Bihar CM Nitish Kumar's mental health. Kishor alleges Kumar shows signs of cognitive decline and suggests the current administration limits his public appearances to avoid scrutiny.

description: Stock market today: BSE Sensex and Nifty50, the Indian equity benchmark indices, opened in green on Tuesday. While BSE Sensex reclaimed the 78,000 level, Nifty50 was above 23,700.
title: Sensex rises over 200 points; Nifty50 above 23,700
'There should be a limit': Shinde hits out at Kunal Kamra amid 'gaddar' joke row

description: Journalist Jeffrey Goldberg accidentally received classified war plans via a Signal group chat that included top Trump administration officials. The plans detailed the timing and targets of the recent US strikes against Yemen's Houthi rebels.
title: Trump officials 'accidentally' sent war plans to journalist: What was in the texts

description: Several explosions occurred due to a fire in a truck carrying LPG cylinders near the Dharavi bus depot in Mumbai. Over 20 gas cylinders exploded, lighting up the night sky and damaging nearby vehicles. Fortunately, no injuries were reported, though the incident caused significant concern among residents.
title: Watch: Mumbai's Dharavi shaken as 20+ LPG cylinders on truck explode

description: India has firmly dismissed Pakistan's repeated claims on Jammu and Kashmir at the United Nations, reiterating that J&K is an integral part of India. India criticized Pakistan for its divisive agenda and called for Pakistan to vacate the illegally occupied region. The Indian representative emphasized that India's stance remains unchanged despite Pakistan's continuous attempts to mislead the international forum.
title: 'Illegal': India rejects Pakistan's 'repeated references' to J&K at UN

description: US President Donald Trump announced 25% tariffs on imports from countries purchasing Venezuelan oil and gas, potentially affecting India, China, and others. These tariffs aim to exert economic pressure on Venezuela, which Trump accuses of hostility and other malpractices. The tariffs, effective from April 2, coincide with his broader plan for reciprocal tariffs on other nations.
title: Trump to impose tariffs on nations buying Venezuelan oil. Will it impact India?

description: Wayne Gretzky, the legendary hockey player, had his nameplate added to a 20-foot goal lamp celebrating Team Canada during the 2016 World Pond Hockey Championships. The lamp traveled across Canada, honoring the country's passion for hockey, and eventually reached the North Pole.
title: Wayne Gretzky’s legacy honored with iconic Goal Lamp at North Pole

description: Maharashtra chief minister Devendra Fadnavis explained the split between BJP and Shiv Sena in the 2014 state assembly elections was due to seat-sharing disagreements and Shiv Sena's refusal to accept the proposed arrangement. Despite separate contests, they eventually joined forces post-election, with BJP leading the government and Shiv Sena as a key ally.
title: Why BJP-Shiv Sena alliance talks fell apart in 2014? Fadnavis reveals backstory
Andhra man found dead in Texas, suicide suspected

description: Yunseo Chung, a 21-year-old Columbia University student, is suing the Trump administration after ICE attempted to deport her despite her lawful resident status. Chung claims this is part of a broader effort to suppress pro-Palestinian activism among university students.
title: Columbia student, in US since childhood, sues Trump admin to stop deportation

description: Stock market recommendations: RBL Bank and ACC are recommended stocks to buy today by Somil Mehta of Mirae Asset Sharekhan. RBL Bank is anticipated to retrace to Rs 205, while ACC is expected to rebound to Rs 2185.
title: Top stocks to buy today: Stock recommendations for March 25

description: Netflix co-CEO Ted Sarandos makes his acting debut in Apple TV+'s new series 'The Studio.' Created by Seth Rogen, the satirical comedy features Sarandos playing himself in a Golden Globes scene. Sarandos praised the collaboration, emphasizing his eagerness and focus on professionalism during the role.
title: Netflix CEO makes acting debut with Apple TV+ series; premieres on March 26

description: Aasif Sheikh, known for his role in Bhabiji Ghar Par Hain!, suffered a severe back spasm and sciatica pain while shooting for the show's film. He was brought to Mumbai in a wheelchair and is receiving steroid injections and painkillers. The actor hopes to recover soon with complete bed rest and resume shooting.
title: Exclusive: Bhabiji Ghar Par Hain actor Aasif Sheikh on battling severe back spasm

description: Project Clay, co-founded by Dyumna Madan and Shivom Sood, impressed on Shark Tank India 4, securing investment from Namita Thapar. Their platform connects students with university mentors, showing significant growth. Thapar's investment and guidance are expected to accelerate their business trajectory.
title: 'Didn't treat us as kids': Dyumna Madan on Sharks' approach towards young

description: John Abraham's film 'Diplomat', which released on March 14, has gained momentum in its second week due to positive word of mouth. Based on a true event, the movie's total collection stands at Rs 26.55 crore by the end of the second Monday, despite a significant drop in earnings on that day.
title: 'Diplomat' box office collection day 11

description: A woman and her mother are accused of killing a realtor in Bengaluru due to years of harassment. The realtor, with a history of deceit, had forced his way into the woman's life and continued to torment her and her family, prompting them to retaliate.
title: 'Drugged him & stabbed in neck': How wife, mother-in-law killed Bengaluru realtor

description: The Union health ministry's department of health and family welfare faces a significant staff shortage with 29% of positions vacant. The parliamentary standing committee has urged the ministry to expedite the recruitment process. There is also an emphasis on increasing the department's technological proficiency.
title: 29% of posts lying vacant in health & family welfare department
8 CPM men get life terms for killing defector to Kerala BJP

description: Uddhav Thackeray has defended comedian Kunal Kamra for calling deputy chief minister Eknath Shinde a 'traitor,' stating Kamra expressed public sentiment. Thackeray criticized the attack on Kamra's studio, urging the government to compensate him, similar to compensation given for the Nagpur riots.
title: 'A traitor is a traitor': Uddhav Thackeray backs comic Kunal Kamra

description: A group dressed as sanitation workers launched an attack on YouTuber Savukku Shankar's Chennai home, dumping waste and threatening his mother. The incident appears to be revenge for Shankar's alleged remarks about sanitation workers, prompting widespread condemnation and demands for justice from the Tamil Nadu government.
title: Mob in janitor uniform storms Chennai YouTuber's home, dumps human excreta
Nifty regains 2025 losses, sensex just 50 points shy
SC intervening in matters that it shouldn't, says BJP MP

description: In Bharuch district, Gujarat, portions of six houses in Kareli village were demolished by the family of a married woman after she eloped with a divorced man from the village. The woman's family took this action when the man's family could not produce him. Police arrested six people, including the bulldozer driver.
title: Woman elopes, her kin hire JCB to raze homes of lover’s family in Gujarat
